p The Testimonial custom post type allows you to add, organize, and display your testimonials. It is provided by <a href="#jetpack">Jetpack</a> plugin.

p First you will need to enable this post type in <a href="#jetpack">Jetpack plugin's</a> options in #[+mark( 'nav', 'Jetpack', 'Settings', 'Writing' )] in order to use it.

p For more information about Jetpack Testimonials please <a href="https://jetpack.com/support/custom-content-types/?aff=6509&cid=588078">visit dedicated information page</a>.

p To display all portfolio projects on your site, you can use a portfolio archive page link in <a href="#navigation">the navigation</a>. Or <a href="https://wordpress.com/support/testimonials/#testimonial-shortcode">Jetpack <code>[testimonials]</code> shortcode</a> to display testimonials on a page.

+tip( 'Renaming the post type' )
	p If you would like to rename this post type, use the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/cpt-editor/"><strong>Custom Post Type Editor</strong></a> plugin. To rename the custom taxonomies related to this post type, use the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/rename-taxonomies/"><strong>Rename Taxonomies</strong></a> plugin.

+tip( 'Custom products order' )
	p For custom posts order you can use a plugin, such as <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/intuitive-custom-post-order/"><strong>Intuitive Custom Post Order</strong></a>.
